int main()
{
	int var = 052;
	printf("%d", var);
	return 0;
}

Place zero before any value and it will become an octal value but not a decimal value.
The following is a conversion of octal value to decimal value:

(5)*(8^1)  + (2)*(8^0)   =  42

Changing the %d to %o will result to 52.

########################################################

#include <stdio.h>

#define STRING "%s\n"
#define KEVIN "Welcome to Kevin Academy!"

int main()
{
	printf(STRING, KEVIN);
	return 0;
}

Result is: Welcome to Kevin Academy!
